<br>
That guy of yours is starting to shape up nicely <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
keylo87,<br>
<br>
As soon as you can pinpoint a location for your character, please do so. This will help others avoid picking the same spot. And I think your character can spot BMXER's sneaky and suspicious guy even if he's not the enemy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
MightyQUEST,<br>
<br>
The reason why artists are asked to pick a location and note it before starting to draw is simple: if they don't note the spot, then someone else might pick it and then we'll end up with characters who are designed for a specific spot and might not work elsewhere.<br>
<br>
So even if you're not sure how fast you can finish your character, it's better to pick a spot than not to <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    This way no one wastes time working on a picture they can't use.<br>
<br>
Also, I haven't set any rigid deadline for finishing this project. It might not go on for months and months, but it's not going to end next week either. There's still plenty of space left in the picture, and the background itself is not finished yet either.<br>
<br>
I've marked down your spot and character <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    The place where he's sitting is a slightly raised concrete base for a yet undrawn rail for the second floor. If you'll hold on for a while, I'll update the background image with the rail in place. This way you can position your character better, and perhaps make him interact with the rail (holding on to it, for example).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Edit</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: I've now added the rail where it belongs. It's placed at the very edge of the concrete base, so if someone's sitting &quot;in front of&quot; the rail they need to hunch down. On the other hand the person sitting there could have their legs dangling over the edge, but their upper body is behind the rail (chin on the rail, sort of).<br>
<br>
This is one of the problems when working with unfinished backgrounds.. There are things missing from them <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Want to color my lineart?</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Otherwise alter something I've created? Please read my <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>profile</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> for further information before proceeding!</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jspuonti>JSPuonti</A> at: 2/23/03 10:56:29 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pofo@polykarbonbbs>pofo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(2/24/03 9:17:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8338.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://w1.185.telia.com/~u18510119/stuff/me~1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Community project thingamajig</span><hr size=1> This seems like a cool project.<br>
